    {
      "step_id": "70d1b54e",
      "step_index": 2,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### Key functional groups / motifs\n- **Cationic basic center:** a **tertiary ammonium** in an **N-methyl piperidinium** ring (`[NH+]1C` indicates it\u2019s protonated/quaternized-like in the input; at minimum it will be **strongly cationic at pH 7.4**).\n- **Large hydrophobic/aromatic system:** a **fused tricyclic aromatic heterocycle** (phenothiazine-like scaffold: two benzene rings fused through **S** and **N** in the central ring; here it\u2019s a **thioether/phenothiazine-type** core).\n- **Thioether substituent:** `CS-` attached to an aromatic ring (adds **lipophilicity** and polarizability).\n- **Flexible linker:** `N-CH2-CH2-CH(*)-` connecting aromatic N to the piperidinium ring (gives **reach** and conformational adaptability).\n- **Structural alerts for hERG:** **cationic amine + polyaromatic hydrophobe** is a classic hERG-binding pharmacophore; phenothiazine-class scaffolds are historically enriched for hERG liability.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T20:03:22.503576+00:00"
    },
    {
      "step_id": "f4a15430",
      "step_index": 3,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### Overall physicochemical \u201cshape\u201d\n- **One strong positive charge** + **bulky, planar aromatic domain** + **flexible side chain** \u2192 matches the common \u201ccation flanked by hydrophobes\u201d pattern.\n- Likely **high cLogP / high aromatic surface area**, and **high polarizability** (sulfur), both often correlate with hERG binding.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T20:03:22.503598+00:00"
    },
    {
      "step_id": "acbcffbc",
      "step_index": 4,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 2) SAR REASONING (why these features matter for hERG)",
