      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T20:03:22.503727+00:00"
    },
    {
      "step_id": "e064db90",
      "step_index": 10,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "- The fused aromatic system is **rigid and planar**, which often helps maintain a consistent hydrophobic binding face.\n- The side chain is **flexible**, enabling multiple binding poses\u2014this generally **increases** the probability of finding a productive hERG-binding conformation.\n- The piperidinium ring will adopt chair conformations; the stereocenter may bias conformer populations, but **it\u2019s unlikely to eliminate** the ability to present the canonical \u201caromatic + cation\u201d geometry.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
